Great game, truly one of a kind. There hasn't been a good 
geopolitical/grand strategy on android before this. What prevents it from 5 
stars is the game-breaking AP bug. As your country's GDP and population 
grows, the AP cost of projects grow proportionately. Well, your AP income 
does not. The result is that a country with big GDP and millions in the 
treasury can afford less and less. You can't have infrastructure, 
healthcare, modern army etc at all. You have to artificially limit the 
growth of the country in order to be able to function later in the game. 
This is counter-intuitive and discourages actually finishing a game. Please 
fix this and I'll upgrade the rating to 5*. Downgraded the rating, because 
the developer doesn't make any effort to fix the game.
